This statement from the White House Press Secretary highlights the President's call with Governors Jindal, Barbour, Riley, and Crist regarding the urgency of dealing with the oil spill. The President reassured the governors that the federal government is bringing the best science and expertise to the table and emphasized the commitment to collaboration with state and local governments. The Department of Homeland Security Secretary, EPA Administrator, and other officials provided a daily briefing on operations, leak stabilization, environmental impact, and oil trajectories. A photograph of the President during the call is also available.